                    <h2>First Place: ASL Recognition Platform</h2>
                    <img src="/img/history/2018_1stPlace.jpg" alt="2018 first place" width="100%">
                    <p>Prize: Monoprice 3-D printer<br><br> Team: Julian Mendel, Mark Nasielski, Serene Kamal, Michelle Du, Eric Sarnoff Espinosa<br><br> Project: With a special glove, users can use sign language to change the color of an LED.<br></p>
                </div>
                <div class="place col-sm-4 text-center">
                    <h2>Second Place: Less Stress Dress</h2>
                    <img src="/img/history/2018_2ndPlace.jpg" alt="2018 second place" width="100%">
                    <p> Prize: Amazon Echo<br><br> Team: Jimmy Byrne, Josh Ren, Anshul Aggarwal, Nina Chikanov, Allison Doami<br><br> Project: Aimed at visually impaired people, this project takes current weather information around the world to choose the perfect outfit for the user.
                </div>
                <div class="place col-sm-4 text-center">
                    <h2>Third Place: Safe Stove</h2>
                    <img src="/img/history/2018_3rdPlace.jpg" alt="2018 third place" width="100%">
                    <p> Prize: Quadcopter drone<br><br> Team: Chris Hailey, Ishan Shah, Joel Joseph, Adithya Bellathur, Janeline Wong<br><br> Project: Using ultrasonic sensors, capacitive touch and facial recognition to reduce the likelihood of cooking fires.</p>
